The Head Office of Unity Bank Plc, a commercial bank, in Victoria Island, Lagos, has been engulfed in an inferno. The incident happened at the early hours of Monday morning. The bank confirmed the incident at about 8 am via its official Twitter handle."We regret to inform the public that there was a fire incident on one of the floors of our head office building early this morning. "The cause of the fire incident has yet to be ascertained but the fire service has intervened and has brought the situation under control. "We are grateful to all the agencies and volunteers that supported in bringing the incident under control. Further developments regarding the incident will be communicated as it unfolds," the bank said.